    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nDid some battle tests of multiple matchparen implementations (vimscript matchparen, new merged lua matchparen, closed PR https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31861, [vim-matchup](https://github.com/andymass/vim-matchup) and mine plugin [matchparen.nvim](https://github.com/monkoose/matchparen.nvim))\n\nI'm using this files for it\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/monkoose/24dbced1234092c7bf186fd2f6875d69 (file with the long line)\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/monkoose/284f02578631d30c487ec239a9f834c7 (file with a lot of curly braces that can be visible on the screen)\n\n**ADDED**: also tested with this javascript file with similar results (except vim-matchup has poor performance in with treesitter highlighting, unlike matchparen.nvim) https://gist.github.com/monkoose/b15955f48e9bf1d69f63e4b163ccd188\n\nUsing D language because it has on of the heaviest treesitter parser in my experience.\nTo be fair setup matchparen.nvim with setup({debounce = 0}) to disable debouncing. (it still has the difference of hardcoded search limit to 150ms and matchparen has configurable option of 300ms by default) but it doesn't really matter for this tests.\n\nFor curly_braces.d file the best test line is 27, 31 and string lines. For 27 and 31 lines put the cursor at the start of it and just hold l and see how fast it starts lagging or stops highlighting.\nOn my PC starting from the worst:\n\nvimscript matchparen (default options):\n- syntax off (line 31): starts lagging immediately.\n- regex syntax (line 27): starts lagging immediately. Highlights wrong brackets inside the string (line 24 and 28).\n- treesitter (line 31): start lagging immediately and skips highlights. Highlights wrong brackets inside the string.\nBottlenecks: vimscript, synstack(), searchpair(), wrong highlights.\n\nClosed PR (default options):\n- syntax off (line 31): starts lagging at the quarter of the line.\n- regex syntax (line 27): starts lagging almost immediately. Highlights wrong brackets inside the string.\n- treesitter (line 31): start lagging immediately Highlights wrong brackets inside the string.\nBottlenecks: synstack(), searchpair(), wrong highlights.\n\nNew lua merged matchparen (default options):\n- syntax off (line 31): starts lagging immediately.\n- regex syntax (line 27): starts lagging at the quarter of the line. Highlights wrong brackets inside the string.\n- treesitter (line 31): start lagging immediately and skips highlights. Highlights wrong brackets inside the string.\nBottlenecks: synstack(), searchpair(), wrong highlights.\n\nvim-matchup (default options):\n- syntax off (line 31): starts lagging immediately.\n- regex syntax (line 27): starts lagging around the half of the line. Right highlights inside strings. Somewhat faster than matchparen.nvim inside strings.\n- treesitter (line 31): start lagging immediately and skips highlights. Highlights wrong brackets inside the string, i guess it is because D language not in it's queries https://github.com/andymass/vim-matchup#tree-sitter-integration (bad implementation relying on queries). Have not tested it in supported languages.\nBottlenecks: synstack(), searchpair() and relying on treesitter queries.\n\nmatchparen.nvim (with debounce = 0):\n- syntax off (line 31): Always responsive.\n- regex syntax (line 27): starts lagging around the half of the line. Right highlights inside strings.\n- treesitter (line 31): Always responsive.\nBottlenecks: synstack(), relying on linear search in regex syntax highlighted buffers.\n\nFor longline.d file all implementations except matchparen.nvim behaves almost the same:\n- syntax off: matchparen.nvim always responsive, others lagging on lines 21 and 23 (closed PR for some reason lags on line 22 col 18 (space char)).\n- syntax on (depends on synmaxcol option): all implementations starts lagging with much lower synmaxcol than matchparen.nvim.\n- treesitter: matchparen.nvim always responsive and highlights. vimscript and new lua matchparens lags and do not highlight brackets on lines 21 and 23. Closed PR lags on lines 21 and 23 but highlights. vim-matchup behaves the same as syntax off because of missing query.\n\nBottleneck for this file is synmaxcol, synstack(), searchpair() and treesitter logic in plugins not skipping nodes and using linear search.\n\nYou can test it yourself (I have somewhat old PC, so your results can differ).\nWith debounce enabled matchparen.nvim feels almost always responsive. It's somewhat extreme examples you not often edit longline files, or files with so much visible brackets, but when you do it really annoying that cursor movement starts lagging because of the one plugin.\n\nFor me if you accepted reimplementation of matchparen plugin without matchit (for some reason clason rejected this idea https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34658) then it would be better to adapt matchparen.nvim for it instead of relying on broken (wrong highlights) and slow old implementation.\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nmatchparen should be faster and highlight right brackets.",
