            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@clason \n\n> The goal is not to upstream a complex plugin but to -- even slightly -- improve the default experience.\n\nmatchparen.nvim not really much more complex than built-in matchparen. Adds caching here and there, debounce feature and  custom alternative to `searchpair()`. Maybe ~ +200 lines.\n\n> And the focus for core is always primarily on basic composable API, not bundled plugins.\n\nI do agree, so maybe improving `searchpair()` is better idea, because it is the bottleneck + adding skipping of treesitter nodes and not relying on linear search.\n\n> Don't cherry-pick bad tree-sitter parsers;\n\nWould test it in some javascript file later.",
