            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Anyway, we'll need to see what the PR looks like. There are lots of awesome plugins that work great but don't fit into core.\n\n💯 \n\nYour insight and experience is very much appreciated, but it is much more useful for us to learn your lessons (_why_ exactly is the legacy matchparen slow? what are the _specific_ fixes you made for each pitfall? can these be applied further up the pipeline so that other features also profit?) than to simply take downstream code as-is. I am especially interested in the correctness problems, as those are much more urgent than performance issues. \n\n(Treesitter can be very slow; that part is well-known and subject of significant improvement efforts both here and upstream. We do _not_ want to paper over it at feature edges instead of addressing the underlying, broader, issues.)",
